Did you know...

Juice cleanses are a dietary “boot camp” where you swear off solid food for a day or two, drink only water and juice, and give your body and gut a major reset. Does it sound tough? It is. Is it worth it? Many swear by it and some fitness experts say they do a juice cleanse a few times every year. 

Many fitness and wellness advocates, avid juicers, and even some doctors note that a juice cleanse can help you temporarily lose weight, help you eliminate unhealthy and processed foods from your diet, and promote better gut health by rebalancing your gut microbiome. 

If you’re looking to eliminate processed foods or other foods from your diet, a juice cleanse might be just the boost you need!

The more fruits and vegetables you include in your juice concoctions, the better the balance of nutrients and minerals will be. Country Farms Super Cleanse contains 34 fruits and vegetables with aloe, so it provides a great supplement alternative for your juicing cleanse. (You can also use it regularly to keep your body detoxified and cleansed naturally.)
 
So if you're choosing to go on a juice cleanse because you had a little too much to drink over the holiday or weekend, Country Farms Super Cleanse is a great choice for that too!
